      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Gwenorgan wrote:</div><div class="orig">Nice, be able to run older content and not see useless badges piling up. I really should look at getting another BoA set from what I do have though, I'm sure on a couple toons that I'll be at or near capped pretty quickly.  <br /> <br />Does leave me wondering what we'll use to buy badge of Justice quality items with though, the new currency that's best suited to our end-game? flat out gold purchase? Not that I've used Justice quality stuff, I don't think I bought more than a piece or 2 of it when it came out on the one character who was high enough. </div></div> <br /> <br />Most likely, item prices will scale. <br /> <br />Maybe BoJ items could be 1-5 JP (Justice Points obviously) each, while Heroism/Valor items might be 6-10 points each, maybe Conquest could be 11-15, Triumphs 16-20, and Frost could be up to 25. <br /> <br />Maybe when Cataclysm comes out, that stuff could be 30-40JP or more. <br /> <br /><s>Theoretically, you could grind Karazhan every week, and if each boss gave you 1JP, you could get a single Cataclysm item, but it'd take you nearly a month of grinding Karazhan to do it, lol. <br /> <br />That's assuming they don't take a large jump up. They could make every Cataclysm item take 500JP or more (obviously, Cata bosses would give more JP than BC or Wrath ones would), then you'd be doing Karazhan for the rest of your WoW career just to get 1 Lv85 purple.</s> <br /> <br />Edit: No, actually, you can't. It says &quot;Level Appropriate&quot; ... I assume &quot;Must be Green&quot; to get points. <br /> <br />I think the JP system is ingenious, and they should have just done that all along. They had the right idea back in BC when everything cost Justice Badges, but the problem is, it was all static in that 1 boss = 1 justice badge until you get into raids, then you start seeing 2 badges after Attumen. <br /> <br />What we needed was a points system, and bosses could be worth different points. Instead, they gave us tiered badges in Wrath (and made some obsolete) and then we had the &quot;must downgrade emblems to buy older stuff&quot; yadda yadda. <br /> <br />The points system will remove a lot of this, and allow them to play around a bit more with what gives what, and what costs what, and keep the system nice and smooth (instead of having a sudden jump, like when heroics suddenly gave Conquest instead of Heroism). Periodically, they could slash 10% off of the cost of outdated items if they wanted to progress the whole game ahead 1 raid tier, for example. <br /> <br />Also, some Librams, Idols, and Totems are nice in that they give awesome ability upgrades in Wrath. I wouldn't be surprised if some of these still saw use into much of Cataclysm, even for a newly-85. Getting these would be easy as pie if a Wrath item cost 20JP and you get 10+ out of one boss. <br /> <br />Assuming, of course, they don't do a massive overhaul to the Idol/Sigil/etc system. <br /> <br />Same goes for trinkets, especially ones that have nice procs. Trinkets are usually difficult to come by, and the main reason people didn't grind up BC trinks to start Wrath endgame, was because nobody felt like grinding BC heroics for JBs. That shouldn't be an issue with the introduction of a universal currency. <br /> <br />Edit2: If _all_ dungeons (even low-level ones) gave even a small amount of JP (even if it is 1-2 points per boss), then one could reasonably build up JP on their way up to Lv80+ if they got into dungeon groups frequently, and be able to buy an item or two on the way up, esp aforementioned trinkets/relics. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Sep 14th 2010  1:48pm by Lyrailis </span></i> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Sep 14th 2010  1:52pm by Lyrailis </span></i></div>
