      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Anobix wrote:</div><div class="orig"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Bashiok wrote:</div><div class="orig">One change of note since that original announcement is that we've changed the name of the low-tier PvE currency from Hero Points to Justice Points. The original announcement post has been updated to reflect this. <br /> <br />Out With the Old <br /> <br />In the upcoming 4.0 patch we'll begin the first stage of the conversion to the new currencies. Emblems of Triumph and Emblems of Frost will be converted into Justice Points. For this initial conversion there will be a soft cap of points you can have, with a hard cap enforced later as detailed below. All PvE emblems and badges below Frost and Triumph will be converted into gold. This even includes legacy badges, like Badges of Justice. If any of these older currencies are converted into gold, the player will receive it through an in-game letter. <br /></div></div></div></div> <br /> <br />I like the idea of converting even the legacy badges, but did they really have to call them &quot;Justice Points&quot; or &quot;Hero Points&quot;? It just seems so corny to me. <br /> <br /><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>------ <br /><a href="http://wow.allakhazam.com/profile.html?2495968" rel="external"><img src="/cgi-bin/wowsig.pl?char=2495968" height="100" width="400" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /></a> <br /><a href="HTTP://www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Nazgrel&amp;n=Danoatnova" rel="external nofollow" title="www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Nazgrel&amp;n=Danoatnova">Danoatnova - 80 Mage</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Nazgrel&amp;n=Westwood" rel="external nofollow" title="www.wowarmory.com/character-sheet.xml?r=Nazgrel&amp;n=Westwood">Westwood - Newly 80 (and neglected) Paladin</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://www.wowarmory.com/character-she