      <div class="msgContentFrame">I like the idea of converting to just 3 currencies.  Initially it will be tricky to value everything properly and some things will be under or overpriced. <br /> <br />The conversion rates and point values assigned to vendor items on the PTR do seem strange.  It's puzzling that they would devalue emblems so much, yet they posted the conversion rates so they must know they are doing it.  Unless an adjustment is made there will be little point to farming emblems before the patch or spending JP after the patch until Cataclysm gear starts showing up at vendors. <br /> <br />If anything it looks like incentive to burn your emblems on gear/crafting mats now even though it/they will be outdated soon and spend your remaining time in wrath just exploring and doing odds and ends. <br /> <br />One small bonus to this system is that one day, after we've all spent tens of thousands of JP/VP on 85 gear and are sitting at the hard cap again, we can go back and buy a <i>bunch</i> of tacky, crappy, presumably really cheap level 70 gear with our JP and strut around in it.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Homer no function beer well without.</div></div>
